      "text": "Virtue is its own reward: that is true. But only insofar as one is conscious of it, to the extent that one can say with conviction I am virtuous. And how many are there who can do this? Is our ability to judge concerning ourselves more reliable [fester] than that concerning other things? Is not the uncertainty in which we find ourselves with respect to our own worth one of the most secret evils that presses upon us; one of the most hidden causes of displeasure and discontentment?",
